President Barack Obama has proclaimed June 2015 as National Caribbean-American Heritage Month. The proclamation highlights the contributions of Caribbean Americans to the United States, emphasizing their rich culture and heritage. The president also emphasizes the shared history and future between the United States and the Caribbean, calling for continued support and partnership. The proclamation also touches on immigration policies, such as the DACA policy, that have allowed Caribbean immigrants to contribute to the country's economy. The president encourages all Americans to celebrate and honor the history and culture of Caribbean Americans during this month.